# TypeScript Standards

- Prefer `interface` for object shapes; use `type` for unions/intersections/aliases.
- Use shared types from `@/lib/supabase/types` for DB-backed entities (Profile, Tenant, TenantMember, etc.); keep API/component props typed explicitly.
- Avoid `any`; use `unknown` and narrow, or proper types.
- Prefer `async/await` over raw Promises; surface errors (throw or return result objects) instead of swallowing.

```typescript
// Prefer
const data = await getTenant(slug);
if (!data) throw new Error("Tenant not found");

// Avoid
getTenant(slug).then((d) => { ... }).catch(() => {});
```
